==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Selenio-
<hw>Se*le"ni*o-</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A combining
form (also used adjectively) denoting the <sig>presence of
selenium</sig> or <xex>its compounds</xex>; <as>as,
<ex>selenio</ex>-phosphate, a phosphate having selenium in place of all,
or a part, of the oxygen</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Selenious</ent>⟦br⟧
